       <section>
            <div class="types" style="text-align: center; width: 1300px">
                <h2 style="color: blue;">Types of cancer</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="cards1" style="width: 1130px;">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="lung-image">
                        <img src="~/Images/lung_cancer.jpg" width="200px" height="200px" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="lung-des">
                        <p>
                            Lung cancer<br /> is the uncontrolled growth
                            of<br /> abnormal cells in one or both of <br />the lungs. These cells are normal
                            that<br /> do not develop into normal lung cells.<br />
                            Tumors form and impede lung function.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="colon-image">
                        <img src="~/Images/colon_cancer.jpg" width="200px" height="200px" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="colon-des">
                        <p>
                            Colon cancer<br /> is a cancer that affects the large<br />
                            intestine (colon), which represents the <br />
                            lower part of the human digestive<br /> system,
                            as well as the rectum,<br /> which is the last part
                            of the <br />digestive system. or greater.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="liver-image">
                        <img src="~/Images/liver_cancer.jpg" width="200px" height="200px" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="liver-des">
                        <p>
                            Hepatocellular carcinoma<br /> is cancer that
                            begins in the cells<br /> of the liver.
                            The liver is<br /> a football-sized organ
                            located in <br />the upper right part of the abdomen,<br />
                            below the diaphragm and above<br /> the stomach.
                            Many types of cancer can<br /> form in the liver.

                        </p>
                    </div>

                </div>
                <div class="clear"></div>


            </div>
            <div class="cards2" style="width: 20000px">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="tract-image">
                        <img src="~/Images/biliary_tract_cancer.jpg" width="200px" height="200px" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="tract-des">
                        <p>
                            Cholangiocarcinoma <br />is a type of cancer
                            that forms in the thin<br /> tubes (ducts of the gallbladder)<br />
                            that carry digestive fluid from the gallbladder.<br />
                            Gallbladder ducts connect the <br />liver to the gallbladder and small intestine.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="kidney-image">
                        <img src="~/Images/kidney_cancer.jpg" width="200px" height="200px" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="kidney-des">
                        <p>
                            Kidney cancer<br /> is the abnormal growth
                            and uncontrolled<br /> proliferation of cells
                            in the kidney,<br /> which is a member of the
                            urinary<br /> system in which urine is made and the<br />
                            body gets rid of waste through it.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="pancreas-image">
                        <img src="~/Images/pancreas_cancer.jpg" width="200px" height="200px" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="pancreas-des">
                        <p>
                            Pancreatic cancer<br /> occurs when cells
                            in the pancreas<br /> develop changes
                            (mutations) in their DNA.<br /> A cell's DNA
                            contains the instructions<br /> that tell the
                            cell what to do.<br /> These mutations tell cells to
                            grow<br /> uncontrollably and to continue living after<br />
                            healthy cells have died.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="clear"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="cards3" style="width: 20000px">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="melanoma-image">
                        <img src="~/Images/melanoma_cancer.jpg" width="200px" height="200px" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="melanoma-des">
                        <p>
                            Skin cancer<br /> is defined as an abnormal
                            growth<br /> of skin cells, and it often occurs <br />
                            when the skin is exposed to harmful<br /> sunlight,
                            but skin cancer can occur in <br />different areas
                            of the body that may<br /> not normally be exposed
                            to sunlight,<br /> such as the genital area and buttocks.<br />
                            It usually occurs on sun-exposed  <br />areas of the body
                            such as the ears or face.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="thyroid-image">
                        <img src="~/Images/thyroid_cancer.jpg" width="200px" height="200px" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="thyroid-des">
                        <p>
                            Thyroid cancer<br /> is a malignant tumor
                            of the thyroid<br /> gland, which is a rare
                            type of cancer.<br /> Not every enlargement
                            in the neck means<br /> the presence of cancer,
                            and a doctor<br /> should be visited to make
                            sure of it.<br /> Hypothyroidism or hyperactivity
                            of the<br /> thyroid gland does not<br /> increase the incidence of cancer.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="brain-image">
                        <img src="~/Images/brain_cancer.jpg" width="200px" height="200px" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="brain-des">
                        <p>
                            brain tumors<br /> is a mass or growth of abnormal<br />
                            cells in the brain. There are<br /> different types
                            of brain tumors.<br /> Some are noncancerous (benign),
                            and<br /> some are cancerous (malignant).<br /> A brain tumor
                            may begin in an area<br /> of ​​the brain (primary brain tumor),<br />
                            or cancer may begin elsewhere in<br /> the body and spread to
                            the brain <br />as secondary (metastatic) brain tumors.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
